children.html:
Gary Vaynerchuk, is a "serial entrepreneur" and business guru, motivational speaker, "5 times New York Times best seller".
        He became an Internet celebrity by starting the first wine vlog. He is now posting hundreds
        of self-help videos in his unique full-on, fast-paced style.
        "work harder", "do your thing", "stop caring about what others think",
        are some of the recurrent themes of his motivational gospel.

How many people, by show of hands, work in a job and are desperate
        for their side hustle to become their career?
        [...]
        Like who the hell's permission are you looking for to do your thing?
        Is it your mum? Is it society? Is it your partner? Is it people commenting in your social media?
        Is it something that happened to you when you were nine?
        [...]
        Go do your thing! You're gonna die! It's going to end! Something bad is gonna happen!
        Something great is gonna happen! But most of all, nothing is gonna happen unless you do something.
        Please stop looking for permission!
It baffles me how many people think that they're bigger than they already are ...
